":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rfjs1m/c_most_important_complexities","submitter_user":{"username":"raymii","created_at":"2013-11-20T11:58:43.000-06:00","is_admin":false,"about":"🐋\r\nhttps://raymii.org","is_moderator":false,"karma":24259,"avatar_url":"/avatars/raymii-100.png","invited_by_user":"journeysquid"},"user_is_author":false,"tags":["c++"]},{"short_id":"bzcqjr","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/bzcqjr","created_at":"2023-11-15T02:42:13.000-06:00","title":"Why did Linux choose Rust but not C++?","url":"","score":33,"flags":0,"comment_count":60,"description":"\u003cp\u003eWhat are the reasons for choosing Rust over C++ as the second language for the Linux project? There is this famous rant [1] of Linus with regards to C++ where he complains that the language is too complicated to be used as a kernel language and its standard library is not stable.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBSDs also did not want to mix C and C++ for kernel programming for various reasons, sticking with one language for the kernel (assembly excluded).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThat being said, what are the advantages of Rust compared to C++ that make it a better candidate for being a kernel language? Besides the technical aspects, does the popularity of Rust also play a role in this choice?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[1] \u003ca href=\"https://harmful.cat-v.org/software/c++/linus\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://harmful.cat-v.org/software/c++/linus\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"What are the reasons for choosing Rust over C++ as the second language for the Linux project? There is this famous rant [1] of Linus with regards to C++ where he complains that the language is too complicated to be used as a kernel language and its standard library is not stable.\r\n\r\nBSDs also did not want to mix C and C++ for kernel programming for various reasons, sticking with one language for the kernel (assembly excluded).\r\n\r\nThat being said, what are the advantages of Rust compared to C++ that make it a better candidate for being a kernel language? Besides the technical aspects, does the popularity of Rust also play a role in this choice?\r\n\r\n[1] https://harmful.cat-v.org/software/c++/linus","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/bzcqjr/why_did_linux_choose_rust_not_c","submitter_user":{"username":"lucic71","created_at":"2022-12-03T09:38:05.000-06:00","is_admin":false,"about":"","is_moderator":false,"karma":94,"avatar_url":"/avatars/lucic71-100.png","invited_by_user":"bsandro"},"user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","c","c++","rust"]},{"short_id":"foo1n7","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/foo1n7","created_at":"2023-11-14T13:55:15.000-06:00","title":"We Need to Bring Back Webrings","url":"https://arne.me/articles/we-need-to-bring-back-webrings","score":69,"flags":0,"comment_count":50,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/foo1n7/we_need_bring_back_webrings","submitter_user":{"username":"bahlo","created_at":"2021-05-09T06:38:47.000-05:00","is_admin":false,"about":"","is_moderator":false,"karma":220,"avatar_url":"/avatars/bahlo-100.png","invited_by_user":"stapelberg","github_username":"bahlo"},"user_is_author":true,"tags":["web"]},{"short_id":"njzpyq","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/njzpyq","created_at":"2023-11-15T03:45:01.000-06:00","title":"i accidentally a scheme","url":"https://wingolog.org/archives/2023/11/13/i-accidentally-a-scheme","score":32,"flags":0,"comment_count":4,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/njzpyq/i_accidentally_scheme","submitter_user":{"username":"river","created_at":"2016-04-03T11:33:05.000-05:00","is_admin":false,"about":"(Deleted account)","is_moderator":false,"karma":6731,"avatar_url":"/avatars/river-100.png","invited_by_user":"355E3B"},"user_is_author":false,"tags":["compilers","lisp","science"]},{"short_id":"mllrju","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/mllrju","created_at":"2023-11-16T06:09:27.000-06:00","titl